name: cystathionine beta-synthase
comment: A pyridoxal-phosphate protein. A multifunctional enzyme: catalyses beta-replacement reactions between L-serine, L-cysteine, cysteine thioethers, or some other beta-substituted alpha-L-amino acids, and a variety of mercaptans.

orthologs.K10150: cysteine synthase / O-phosphoserine sulfhydrylase / cystathionine beta-synthase
